                    <p>An antibody test is a screening for antibodies in blood. It is also &nbsp;called a serology test.The antibody test isn’t checking for the virus itself. Instead, it looks to see whether your immune system — your body’s defense against illness — has responded to the infection.</p>
                    <h4><strong>What’s the Difference Between a Coronavirus Test and an Antibody Test?</strong></h4>
                    <p>A coronavirus test, sometimes called a diagnostic test, looks for signs of active virus. It’s simpler and faster than an antibody test. But it tells you only if you have the virus in your body at the moment when you’re tested.An antibody test shows that you had the virus at some point in the past. It could be gone, or you could still be contagious.</p>
